Best Pakistani/Indian food in California. I've had it all and this is the closest to Lahore chole you can get. Fish pakora also best I've ever had. If I had to recommend anything it would be shrimp cur-eye (not sure how it's spelled not curry) and the chole with some beef of chicken kababs. If you are new to Indian food they have awesome lamb chops as they a more mild on the spices and my girlfriend absolutely loves them!< /Text>

< text>
This restaurant is a great addition to Sacramento‚Äôs Indian Cuisine. I‚Äôve been here a few times and sampled several different dishes now before writing this review. The food is flavorful, consistent, and always fresh. The staff here is also a highlight of the restaurant. I am always promptly greeted and seated. They always have a smile on their face. I‚Äôve never had to wait long for my food or for service. Lastly, their catering prices are competitive. I haven‚Äôt had a chance to order catering yet, but I‚Äôm sure if the same chefs are cooking, it‚Äôll be excellent. Overall, this place is a must if you‚Äôre in this area of Sacramento.</text>

<user_id>115477950405809293084< /user_id><Name>Charity Baldwin<//Name>< time>
1559351755149< /time>
< rate>
3<//rate>
< review>
The restaurant was pleasant and clean and surprisingly large. It was mostly empty but we got takeout anyway. The waiter (?) was very polite and friendly as well.

The reason for the 3 stars is the actual food.

It wasn't bad but I've had better. I had Thai basil chicken and garlic naan, my husband had chicken tikka masala with keema naan. The Thai basil was good. The tikka masala was very spicy and it just wasn't great. Both naans were rubbery.

If you're in the area it's not a bad place to eat but I've had these dishes many times at various places and I just wasn't wowed by it.</review>

< Review>
Chester is a small town, not too many choices for restaurant food, but Happy Garden is truly top notch and would hold its own anywhere in Northern California, including a big city. The staff is so friendly!

We particularly enjoy their salt and pepper ribs, their daily specials, and their limited-but-excellent dim sum menu. We look forward to the end of Covid when it's safe to dine indoors. Very cute atmosphere.  Sweet place.< /Review>

<Text>Just got back from Subway and had a potential bad experience turned into a 5 star experience because of the quality service that was given to me by the man in charge.
As I entered this establishment, only one other person was in line ordering and one person on the serving side taking this customer's order. The only other employ that I believed was there 2as stocking chips right next to me. The gentleman behind the counter asked the young lady stocking chips to come back and help out. It was at this point I realized she was a new hire.probably her first day. I am the first to understand how nervous a person can get on their first of a new job, especially if it could be your first ever job. As I told her what my order was and watched her make my order, I realized she might have tunnel vision right now. Not only did she not hear what I had asked, she only put enough meat for a 6" sub let alone a foot long. I Kinsley informed her that there wasn't enough meat on the sandwich and it just wasn't registering with her. So, as I was checking out, in my frustration of trying to be as nice as possible, informed the gentleman in charge that my order is on the slim side. He promptly made a new one and handled with the greatest of professionalism. I am impressed as it is hard to find these days. As far as the young lady that was starting her new job, she will be just fine when she gets the groove of things and has an awesome instructor to guide her into being a confident employee.

THANK YOU</Text>< pictures>

< Review>
This is the third CX-5 in a row that my wife and I have leased from Neftin Mazda--and for good reasons. Our latest experience with this dealership continues a pattern of delightful experiences. Danny Schaefer, the Sales Manager, put numbers together (without the need to negotiate and without pressure) that made it possible to get a better equipped CX-5 below the amount we expected to pay: 2021 CX-5 Grand Touring AWD Deep Crystal Blue with the Premium Package and with black leather. As to the CX-5, there've been enough subtle improvements to the point where we again got far more than we expected in the new vehicle. </record></dataset><record>
<text>This is a difficult review to write, my experience with Neftin started out really strong and then cratered. I want to cover the good point first. Cynthia was an excellent salesperson, she answered tons of questions, found the car I wanted, and did her best with a situation that quickly started spiraling down.

Onto the bad. The car I got was part of a dealer trade, and had to be driven up to Neftin. The first inspection of the car as a once over was fine, but prior to purchasing we went over it in more depth. There as large chip on the door edge (down to the metal) near the driver side door handle, a large scratch on the gas cap, and two chips on the front bumper.  On pointing them out I was assured they could be fixed.  I should have backed out then, but after the work Cynthia had put in to find and get the car I decided to move forward.  Paperwork was fine, signed on the dotted line. Took it home for a few days before bringing it back for the paint repairs. It went downhill from there.  This was 3/25.

The first repair was delayed due to an internal error, I was offered a free Xpel clear bra and door trim due to the error.  It was also offered as it was a chip repair, not a full paint. After a few days I got the car back and the chip repair was terrible. It was explained to me that the chip needed to cure and then be brought back to be leveled/smoothed out.  The bumper had no work done, the gas cap was fixed. They also would not hold the car at the time as they didn't have garage space.  While this did not make a ton of sense to me, I took the car home.  During this time I also worked with the dealership and the wrapping service to add some additional Xpel layers on my dime, this included putting down my own deposit.  We got the car back 4/2.

Because the Xpel layer was coming, I didn't want to risk any further paint damage, plus the chip on the door made me nervous, so the car stayed in a garage.  Took it back on the 6th.

I went to pick up the car on the 9th and it looked worse than when it went in. The chip was still there, but now it has bubbled edges. The bumper was not repaired at all, and even had an orange spot now. The Xpel was intended to cover these flaws up. I refused to take the car in that shape. The manager came out, agreed the work was shoddy and they kept the car to decide on the best method of repair. It was decided on Monday that the car would go for a full repaint on the door and bumper.  During that conversation it was relayed to me that the dealership would no longer cover their portion of the Xpel coverage. So I've not had my car a long period of time, a service that was offered as compensation for a delay has been removed, and I've already put a deposit down on additional services that I have to cover more costs to complete.

I spoke with the wrap team and they won't be able to do any work on the car for three weeks to ensure the paint is fully set.

I finally get the car back on the 16th.   For those keeping track that's three weeks it's been in and out of the shop.

As of now my car is still sitting in a garage because I don't want to risk any additional paint damage before the clear coat.  None of these delays would have been needed if the dealership had been honest about what the repairs would take, and fixed it properly the first round.   They could have reduced the sales price of the car initially as well, or found another one. I was a guaranteed sale, but did have to have the car right now.  This was my first new car in ten years, and this was an extremely sour experience, it sucked all the joy out of getting a new car.

We will never return to this dealership. I would recommend if your car is coming from another dealership as part of a trade make sure to go over it in detail, and do not accept it if there are any issues with a promise of a fix.

<Review>My background: I'm a mechanical engineer. This is by far the worst car-buying experience I've ever had. Come to Neftin Westlake for the authentic 3rd rate New Jersey used car lot experience.

Since purchasing a vehicle here, I've had (within 5,000 miles of purchase):
-Suspension issues (I suspect a worn bushing, started hearing it clunk around almost immediately)
-Transmission issues (sticks in gear, again within a month of purchase)
-To remove wax from my plastic trim and headlights, and re-polish the paint since it was clearly hit with a dirty buffing wheel. I believe this was a gift from their "touch up" while I was signing paperwork.
-Have the hood latch adjusted so I could actually close it (The sales manager insisted he had done his due diligence on the vehicle immediately after this fix. Hilarious after driving down the interstate with a loose hood on a 1 month old "Certified" vehicle.)
-Have a suspicious dent in the hood from someone clearly trying to force it closed due to the maladjusted latch (I believe this was also a gift from their "touch up" while I was signing paperwork).

I'm kind of wondering what the Culver City dealership will find when they flush the transmission. I half expect sawdust at this point.

If this is what they sign off on for CPO, steer EXTREMELY clear.< /Review><Pics>None</Pics><resp>{'time': 1580335700099, 'text': 'Steve, Our goal is to make sure each certified car is in excellent condition. We are known for our honesty and integrity in the community and would never do anything to sabotage or damage a vehicle as you implied.\n\nWhen you brought back your Mazda 3 on 10/15/2019, two months after purchase, regarding the hood latch and painting the hood, we were happy to fix the latch but would not paint the hood as it was covered in damaging tree sap. < Text>
I worked with Cynthia in the internet sales department when I bought my new 2016 MX-5 Sport. It was without a doubt the best car buying experience I've ever had. I sent Cynthia an e-mail asking for a quote and she got me a great price on the car.

I am very particular when I buy a new car, and she was totally accommodating with all of my needs. I asked that she verify the odometer reading and that the car had not been test driven before, and specifically requested that the car not be washed so I could hand it directly over to my detailing guy. None of those things were an issue - she verified the odometer for me and secured the keys to the car in her office. I hopped in the car and drove over two hours to Neftin Mazda to pick up my new car. Absolutely worth the drive!

I'd test driven the new MX-5s at a few dealerships so I didn't feel the need to drive the car I'd be buying, but I inspected everything carefully and the car was perfect. I met Cynthia when I arrived and she's by far the most friendly and humorous sales person I've ever dealt with. We sat down and filled out the paperwork (which was a breeze!), took care of the financing side, and Cynthia even followed me to the gas station as I had requested to be the one that drives the car off the lot. I drove off with the biggest smile on my face in my new MX-5!

Let's review. Cynthia responded immediately to my calls and e-mails, is a Mazda enthusiast herself and is extremely passionate about the cars she sells, has encyclopedic knowledge of every new Mazda vehicle, has a fantastic sense of humor, and was completely straightforward and forthcoming throughout the entire purchase process. I might have to buy another Mazda just so I can work with her again!

It's not just her either. All of the other staff at Neftin Mazda were an absolute pleasure to work with, and the dealership itself is very nice. Everything is kept very clean and organized inside and the premises look great too.

All in all, I'd give far more than five stars if I could. If you're in the market for a new or used Mazda, send Cynthia an e-mail or give her a call and you'll never be disappointed. Hands down the best Mazda dealer in Southern California.< /Text>

<text>Arrived at Richmond CA Costco at 7:55 today for first day of Senior Shopping Hour between 8 & 9. Longer line than I expected! Employees had line under control and got us inside pretty quickly. Given a wipe at the door to clean the cart handle and my hands. Once inside about the same crowd as a regular Costco day. Even scored some toilet paper, but they were all out of it by 8:55 when I left. Limited to one package per person. Well stocked with most items. All registers open and most had no line behind the person being checked out. Thanked every employee I passed by and each was appreciative of the acknowledgement that they were all working hard. All in all, a smooth shopping experience, considering the circumstances and the line to get in.</text>< Pics>

<response>None<//response>< Gmap_id>
0x808578e797263f71:0xaaf976e769f9e272< /Gmap_id>
</record></dataset><record>
< text>
They successfully achieved their goal of deep discount bulk pricing on a wide arrangements of household goods, food, and paper products.  They're $4.99 rotisserie chickens and dollar fifty for hot dog and Coke can't be beat.  Checkout lines are often very long and impossible during the holiday season.  Parking is tight also.  Store is clean.  As typical with Costco there is little or no customer service.  Their pharmacy and optical pricing are very competitive.  Lots of free food samples at the end of each isle.  The annual membership fee is worth it if you use the store more than occasionally or share the card with a friend or are a small businesses.  Super friendly return policy.  televisions and electronics are very competitively priced.  Not worth your time if you're only picking up one or two items.  Good prices on both national brands and Costco's in House Kirkland brand.  Best gasoline prices in the area.< /text>

<userid>118040390113033516659< /userid>< name>
Phirun Cheng< /name>
< time>
1511623757530< /time>
<Rate>5< /Rate>< review>
Beside the general awesomeness that Costco has going for itself consistently, I will just review this location specifically. The staff here are almost always wonderful to work with (of course you'll eventually run into someone who's having a bad day), but always very polite.

The concession food area is generally clean, but considering the foot traffic of that area, it's hard to maintain every single minute, so bring a few napkins to wipe the table if you plan on sitting down to eat. The staff at the concessions are also very efficient and quick, so waiting in a long line shouldn't deter you from getting any food because you'll be up there quicker than you may think.

The bathrooms are clean and well maintained for such a high traffic location.

The selection here is amazing, with special seasonal items offered too, so look out for those because they may be hidden in between the larger always in-stock items.

The only downside to this location is the fact that there aren't many sample stands as the San Leandro location. Unfortunately, there are only a few samples going on and even at its max, it's not as many as the SL location's usual offer. As a vegetarian, it doesn't even matter because it's usually something I cannot eat, but for those omnivores, it's not as fun as trying out all the samples at the SL location.

Regardless, I highly recommend this location for food, gasoline, groceries, and basically everything offered by Costco. Keep a lookout for special seasonal items!< /review>

Busy, getting in and out can be a little convoluted.

<UserId.>108296159243433544974</UserId.><Name>Rodrigo Castellari Affonso<//Name>< Time>
1543420897401</Time>
<rating>5</rating>< review>
Great place for deals. I come primarily to Costco for bulk food (we are just 2, so it's not like you need to run a restaurant or have a family of 4 for it to make sense - just have some space to freeze some stuff) plus Costco is our go-to place when we have friends over or organizing a party (disposable serving stuff and great snacks). Costco also offers great deals in spirits, the only downside is that the bottles are usually huge (1.75L) and come with an ugly handle, so they are not very pretty to display in your home bar. Finally, I monitor their website for electronics deals: they occasionally offer great discounts on high-end products - we just got a surface pro 6 with $300 off.
In just 4 months we have saved much more than their subscription fee so I definitely recommend it for people looking to save money!< /review>

<review>Gas station has 3 pumps on most islands at Richmond location. That really helps speed up the wait. Because each Costco increasingly carries different items at different locations, I am frequently frustrated that I cannot find an item at one Costco that is readily available at another. I understand each Costco now tries to cater more to it's particular geographic and demographic location, so sometimes you can discover something you never knew Costco carries. Be aware it is not always less expensive to buy stuff at Costco than other stores.< /review>< pictures>

< Review>
Typical Costco.  Good prices.  Loads of temptations.  Gas line a mile long.  My only complaint would be the customers.  They block the aisle in the parking lot waiting for a spot near the entrance.  I'm talking about 20 to 30 somethings.  There's always a spot 50 to 100 feet away. Lazy maybe,  or just IQs a little lower than Forrest Gump???

Once inside its almost as bad.  These stores have super wide aisles,  but when a group of 4 or 5 folks with cars decide to stop and chat you finally have to ask them to make way.  The result is usually a dirty look and a 30 second wait while they grudgingly move.

All in all it's not Costco's fault,  just a sign of the deteriorating world we live in.  The prices still make it worth the trouble.</Review>

< review>
I love Costco, and this one here is no exception; it's extremely busy and getting in and out can be a real challenge. About a block before you get to the store, they have a four way stop sign that you have to fend for yourself and don't assume other understand what a stop sign mean.

They do have some slight varieties that the Antioch one doesn't have and this Costco has more "hyper active customers" than the others I've been to.

Their food to go hot dog and pizza area could use a redesign.. the lunch traffic can cause the shopping carts to be backed up.<//review>

101867188288372076107</userid>
<username>Tao<//username><Time>1558402792910</Time>< rating>
1<//rating>
<text>For your vision health, don't go to Costco vision center for lens!

I ordered new lens for my frame. After I got my glass, it was not easy for my eyes to focus on the screen, I could easily get eye strain. Then I went to see the doctor, after examinations, she thought maybe because of the defect of my eyes' muscle, which caused strabismus. But I never had this problem before.

Then I bought a new pair of glass elsewhere, my vision became normal. Then I went to see the doctor again, after examinations, doctor told me my eyes were OK, I didn't have strabismus. The reason for the problem can be caused by the lens I ordered from costco, my frame was not small, and the optical center of the frame was far way from my actual pupils' location, which can cause distortions.

When I ordered the lens, I realized costco even didn't measure my pupils' location when I wear my frames. They just measure the pupil distance. Now I find the reason for eye strain after investigations, but it's already been more than half year since I bought it, so I cannot get any refunds from costco...

Here is my recommendations:
If your prescription is high (my prescription is -4.5 R, -5.0 L), and also your frame is not small, which means when you wear your frame, your pupils are off the geometric center of the frame (actually this is true for most people.) DO NOT go to costco, go to a glass store where they will mark your pupils' location when you wear the frame.

I hope my review can help the people who have the similar symptom after ordering glasses from costco.<//text>< pictures>
None<//pictures>

A veritable jungle of consumer choices, this spectacular palace of products, is more a humanitarian experience  than a shopping trip.
Well paid employees,  and thoughtful shoppers, families mostly who take saving money and planning ahead seriously  are the regulars here, and despite the enormity, a quality I always equated with sub standard products,  CostCo has their formula down pat.  Great deals on meant and staples, as well as a wide variety of consumer electronics,  I pray that they keep a share of the market in a globally amazoning marketplace.

Memberships vary, but start at around $60 a year.
TIPS: Raw honey, Organic Almond butter, and  Prime steaks are always a great deal here.</Review>

<userid>103560484122312886655<//userid><Name>Tatter Salad</Name>< Time>
1431724615299<//Time>
<rate>4</rate>< review>
This Costco is just like any other Costco, only with MANY MORE CUSTOMERS! Their management, and especially the Optomitrist (not necessarily their eye wear department) is WAY above average. Try to avoid the place on weekends. REALIZE that their mark-up ACROSS THE BOARD is a flat 20% (except booze and tires). GREAT prices on electronics and high-end jewelry.
Take careful note of posted prices, as the 'price tags' are coded: ending in .99 is standard mark-up; Price ending in .97 ‚Äì a deal decided by the manager (read: CLEARANCE) Once it's gone it's gone.
Price ending in .49 or .79 ‚Äì manufacturer's special
Price ending in .00 ‚Äî the goods are about to go! Last pallet for example.
Lastly: their Return Policy is as GOOD AS IT GETS, and sometimes the line is as bad as it gets!< /review>

When my time came to give the receipt to the door man. He pulled me to the side and made me empty out the box while he watched and started giving me lectures. He made me feel like I just got caught stealing something. Why didn't cashier say anything if there was some kind of store policy on wine boxes???.</Text>

I would go here more often if it weren't such a cluster to navigate.  Costco either needs to expand this location (they did as much for the gas station here) or build another store nearby.  The next closest are in Hayward and Concord.

What's worse is that the people at Costco who should be reading these reviews are not reading these reviews.  I have been told by many workers at the various bay area costcos I've been to and they all say the same thing: fill out the comment cards near the exit or you won't get your word out.

<UserId.>106170335079428053302<//UserId.><username>Corrie Davidson< /username><Date>1383005270468<//Date>< Rating>
3< /Rating>
< review>
Parking is a bigger challenge than it should be due to the crowds and (relatively) small lot. You have to have a membership to shop here (and a general desire to buy things in bulk). Memberships range between $50-$100 but can pay for themselves depending on what you buy and how often you buy it. They do have amenities like a gas station and tire center, a deli and bakery, an eye doctor, a pharmacy (closed on Sunday) and a photo processing department, so you can get a lot done in one place.</review>

< username>
Elaine White< /username>
<date>1500394871638<//date><rating>1</rating>< text>
I shop at this costco regularly and you pay for the service you get.  With that in mind, I don't take offense with dry attitudes I get from your young female cashiers.
I called the tire shop Saturday to see if I needed an appointment and to get information since this was my 1st time purchasing tires from Costco.  No one ever answered tge phone.
I decided to come in Sunday to check it out.  When I arrived I found great parking , and was able to walk right up to the counter where Chris greeted me.  We reviewed my vehicle and the tire measurments and type I needed.
Chris told me he wouldnt be able to match the same exact tires but he had 2 tires for my car.  Great!  I paid and Chris said it would be 3 hours. Which also makes sense since a line had formed behind me.
I said to Chris before I left everythings good, all season all wheel drive, he said yes.
I forgot to mention 1 last thing about my vehicle and starting it to Chris,  he said no problem they will call you.  He also asked where I parked my car.  I thought it was good, called my Uber and went home.
3 hours later I get a call from Leonard the head mechanic I assume.  He let me know that due to my car being All wheel drive, they could only do all 4 tires since they do not carry that type to match my other 2 tires.  I had the option to purchase 4 tires, but I only need 2.
Leonard was extremely helpful he told me he could get me a refund and apologized.
So another $20 uber ride back to Costco to now pick up my car with no new tires, and hopefully a speedy refund.
I got back to the front desk at costco and there was a woman in front of me and Chris was there to greet me.  Leonard came up and was dealing with a wrong phone number written down from another customer, he took me and skipped the lines and immediately refunded my money!
I went to get my car and realized no one told me where it was parked.  Again went to Chris and he acted like I should know where you all park cars that are ready for pick up, well I dont.
This was my 1st time using the tire shop!  He told me where  my car was after walking up and down the parking lot with an injured knee!

My suggestion after spending $40 on uber and 4 hours of my time to recieve no services is to train Chris on how to identify an issue such as mine before it happens.  If he would've told me the costco tire policies as Leonard did once I had already paid, I wouldnt of left my car here in the 1st place.  Was he trying to push me to buy 4 tires and get it done?  well I'll never know!
In customer service if you notice your wasting someones time and money you wanna take care of them and have sense of urgency.  Leonard knows this, the bad rating is not due to Leomard, tho Chris wasted my money and time!  I will never use costco tires shops and stick to my usual shopping here, and not go back to this location.</text>
